17.4.4.2.21 basic_ostream<charT,baggage>::operator<<(basic_streambuf<charT,baggage>&)

    basic_ostream<charT,baggage>& operator<<(basic_streambuf<charT,baggage>& sb);

A formatted output function, extracts 'character's from the input sequence
controlled by sb and inserts them in *this.  Characters are extracted and
inserted until any of the following occurs:

-- end-of-file occurs on the input sequence;

-- inserting in the output sequence fails (in which case the character to be
inserted is not extracted);

-- an exception occurs (in which case, the exception is rethrown).

If the function inserts no characters, it calls setstate(badbit).  The
function returns *this.


